{
  "texts": [
    "Each input token has two options, corresponding to the presence or absence of particular functional groups in the polymers.",
    "The first token implies whether the polymer contains an ether group, while the second token indicates the presence of carbonate groups.",
    "The minGPT model is trained using labeled p-SMILES codes.",
    "During generation, the model utilizes two input labels as starting tokens to generate the complete polymer sequence.",
    "By manipulating these two input labels, we are able to deliberately generate polymer with ether group but without carbonate group."
  ]
}